Bug ID:024
Title: 24.Adding a location with 0 price gives code 400 and confirmation messege.
Description: Adding a new location with correct name and prices equal to 0 gives you code 400 on the DevTools but you get a "You have successfully added a location" message.

Steps to Reproduce:
Step 1: Open browser and go to (https://lzcbvwog.acmebooking.com/).
Step 2: Log into your account.
Step 3: Click on Add a location in the navbar.
Step 4: Fill in the fields with correct name and prices equal to 0.
Step 5: Click the Add location button.
Step 6: Check the code in the DevTools(F12) in Network.
Step 6 : Affirm the "You have successfully added a location" message.



Expected Result:
When adding a location with a price equal to 0, after getting a code 400 you should get an error message.

Actual Result:
When adding a location with a price equal to 0, you get the "You have successfully added a location" message. But in the DevTools you get a code 400 and your location is not created.

Severity:
High  

Priority:
High

Additional Information:
-

Environment:
Browser: Brave 1.70.119, Mozilla Firefox 130.0.1 (64-bit)
Operating System: Windows 10, Windows 11
Device: Desktop PC
Network:Ethernet
